commit.message:
[doc] Fix parameter name in tutorial_1.rst

This now matches the names of parameters in `tuto_1_2.py`
Updates README.rst with proper code highlight

Remove pip import and version check from setup.py

Changes to how setuptools 50 works means that installing doit crashes with a cryptic KeyError (most likely caused by setuptools and pip’s monkeypatching of distutils). This check is not really necessary (most people have a newer pip these days).

commit.message: fix test: simplify check sqlite3 module not imported if not used.

Replace recursive knot with explicitly unpicklable object

Python 3.8 was able to pickle the previously unpicklable. Instead of
relying on limits, let's raise an explicit error.
